<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER - AIR COMPRESSOR/POWER
        STEERING PUMP (If Applicable)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>AIR COMPRESSOR/POWER STEERING PUMP (If Applicable)</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="7">
            <title>INSTALLATION</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the air compressor/power steering pump as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Apply a small amount of assembly grease to the O-Ring and install into groove on
                        front cover.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Mount air compressor to front cover and attach with capscrews. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050835">8.35</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Place air compressor bracket against crankcase, then slide forward to air compressor
                        mounting face. Install two (2) bolts and finger-tighten to secure bracket to crankcase. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050836">8.36</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1050835" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3010" filename="../figeg3/EG3010.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.35.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Air Compressor</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Front Cover</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Mounting Bolts (2)</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1050836" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3004" filename="../figeg3/EG3004.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.36.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Air Compressor</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Tail Bracket</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Power Steering Pump Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Secure air compressor bracket to air compressor using two (2) bolts and two (2)
                        washers. Tighten to standard torque. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050837">8.37</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Torque two (2) bolts securing bracket to crankcase to special torque value (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050838">8.38</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install two (2) coolant hoses to air compressor and to crankcase (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050839">8.39</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1050837" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3003" filename="../figeg3/EG3003.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.37.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Bracket</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Tail Bracket</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Air Compressor</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1050838" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3011" filename="../figeg3/EG3011.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.38.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Air Compressor</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Tail Bracket Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Tail Bracket</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1050839" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3014" filename="../figeg3/EG3014.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.39.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Coolant Fitting</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Coolant Hose</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Air Compressor</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install lubrication line to air compressor and tighten nuts in two (2) places (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050840">8.40</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Using two (2) bolts, mount steering pump to air compressor (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050841">8.41</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ) and tighten bolts.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef1050840" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3006" filename="../figeg3/EG3006.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.40.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Air Compressor</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Lube Oil Line</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. Nuts (2)</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef1050841" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="eg3013" filename="../figeg3/EG3013.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.41.</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. Air Compressor</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. Power Steering Pump</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
